template.name: Robot

transition.label: !mayContinue
ND[id] = dfs(id), mayContinue = true, DUpdated[id] = true
ND[id] == R
done[id] = true, allDone = count(done) == R ? 1 : 0, sameCycle = allSameTimestamp(cycle), prefsUpdated[id]=true, DUpdated[id]=true
These updates are only for verification (SMC)
mayContinue && publicND[id] != R
updateP(), decision[id] = maxIndex(P[id]), mayContinue = false, prefsUpdated[id] = true, DUpdated[id] = false
mayContinue&&noOneBehindTwo()
publicP[id] = P[id], publicND[id] = ND[id], incrementCycle(), prefsUpdated[id] = false, mayContinue = false, H[id] = Hk(id), entropy = sum (r : robot) H[r]
Removed &&noConNeighBehind() from guard for now

query.comment:
How many cycles in total does robot 0 go through before consensus is reached.

Note 2: Without empirical value (actually 0.1) (and network size 106): 29.51 +- 3.96507

query.comment: It would be nice to have the reverse query. Within this time, how much time does it take at most to reach this state? There should be a few edge cases where a robot takes one more cycle than the others. This is because of unknown interleavings that causes a single robot (seemingly a robot with only one neighbor) to not calculate their decision group size correctly at the first cycle where all robots agree.
